<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, April 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini Saturday
expressed "sincere joy" over a historic agreement aimed at ending
the three-decade-old strife in Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
In a message to his British and Irish counterparts Robin Cook
and David Andrews, Dini praised "the courage, spirit of compromise
and far-sightedness" demonstrated by government and political
leaders of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The peace deal resolving the conflict over British rule of
Northern Ireland was finally struck on Friday by the political
parties involved in the peace talks. (Italy-Northern Ireland)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- At least 15 people were killed in road accidents in
the past two days as people rushed back to their homes in
provinces to celebrate Songkran holiday, the traditional Thai new
year.
</P>
<P>
The highway police division said on Saturday that there had
been 35 road accidents on Friday and 11 people had been reported
killed and 36 injured.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, another four people died and seven others were
injured when an inter-province bus with some 50 passengers on
board overturned in the central Sing Buri province.
 (Thailand-Accident)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- A World War II bomb exploded in front of a group of
students camping in Doyo village, Sentani subdistrict of
Indonesian Irian Jaya province, Friday, instantly killing one
person and seriously injuring 17 others.
</P>
<P>
The victim who died was identified as Jusuf Maweri, and the 17
others are in several hospitals, Antara News Agency reported
Sunday. (Indonesia-Bomb Blast)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Israeli warplanes Sunday carried out a series of air
raids on suspected Lebanese guerrilla positions in south Lebanon,
Lebanese Orient Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Israeli fighters Sunday swooped down on a mountainous area
between the towns of Armetai and Sujud in the eastern sector of an
border enclave occupied by Israel in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The area is believed to be used by the Iranian-backed
Hezbollah guerrillas as a base for operations against Israeli
soldiers and their militia allies South Lebanese Army (SLA).
(Lebanon-Israel-Air raid)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian armed forces Sunday started a 10-day joint
maneuvers in the Persian Gulf and Gulf of Oman in order to
strengthen its defensive capabilities.
</P>
<P>
The war game with the code name of "Ettehad" (Unity) will be
held in three phases on the ground and under water in an area of
15,000 square nautical miles from Iran's southern port of Bandar
Abbas in the Persian Gulf to Chabahar in the Gulf of Oman.
</P>
<P>
For the first time, three Russian-made submarines will also
join the military exercises with two frigates, two personnel
carrier vessels, two logistic vessels and teams of frogmen along
with 15,000 personnel of naval and air forces.
(Iran-Maneuver-Gulf)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistan on Sunday strongly refuted the
allegations of foreign aid to its development of a new surface to
surface missile.
</P>
<P>
"Such reports, emanating from abroad, are not only baseless but
also betray ulterior motives," a Foreign Office spokesman said in
a statement issued here.
</P>
<P>
He was reacting to a report carried by the New York Times on
Saturday that the Hatf-V (Ghauri) missile test-fired by Pakistan
on April 6 was smuggled from the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK). (Pakistan-Spokesman-Missile) 
</P>
