<HEADLINE> Wanda Regains Lead in League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Dalian Wanda
regained their lead in the Chinese first division soccer league
after beating Chinese Army 1-0 in Chongqing on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Wanda, who having never topped the league standings since the
second round, collected 10 points from four games to tie with
Qiangdao Hainiu, who gained as much points from five matches.
</P>
<P>
Hans Eklund of Sweden scored the sole goal of the match with a
47th-minute header from a corner pass by Hao Haidong.
</P>
<P>
The hosts military team popped up for a late comeback when they
almost found the net from two corners but failed to change the
mark.
</P>
<P>
Wanda lost to Pohang Steelers of South Korea in a penalty
shoot-out in the final of the Asian Federation Cup on April 5.
</P>
<P>
In the other match in the city, hosts Vanguards drew with
Shanghai Shenhua 1-1 and dropped to the fourth place in 14-team
standings.
</P>
<P>
The hosts opened the score from a spectacular free kick of Peng
Weiguo in the 49th minute, a goal which floated over the wall and
into the right corner of the net.
</P>
<P>
Shenhua equallized on a low shot from Claudio Morena of Mexico
in the 60 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The two clubs tie at the fourth place on the standings with
eight points respectively.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's other matches, Guangzhou Songri beat Shandong
Luneng 3-2 while Qingdao Hainiu defeated Wuhan Yaqi 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang Haishi drew with Sichuan Quanxing in a goalless game
while Shenzhen Pingan went down to Guangzhou Apollo 2-0 at home.
</P>
<P>
Match between Beijing Guo'an and Yanbian Aodong was postponed
because Guo'an attended the Asian Cup Winners' Cup semi-finals.
</P>
</TEXT>
