<HEADLINE> China Pledges to Help Indonesia Overcome Economic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- China Sunday expressed sympathy
for the Indonesian people over the current monetary crisis in the
country and pledged efforts to help overcome their difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan voiced the
sympathy during a meeting here with his Indonesian counterpart Ali
Alatas.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a joint press conference after the three-hour
meeting, Tang said China will soon provide medicine and food
assistance worth 3 million U.S. dollars to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Alatas said the Indonesian government will receive a 200
million U.S. dollars export credit facility offered by the Chinese
government for a two-year period.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, both sides also agreed to expand bilateral
economic cooperation through barter trade and other trade forms.
</P>
<P>
Alatas said the assistance from China is outside the framework
of the International Monetary Fund (IMF) aid package worth 43
billion U.S. dollar to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Since July last year, Indonesia, along with other Southeast
Asian countries, has been badly hit by the monetary crisis. The
Indonesian rupiah (national currency) has lost more than 70
percent of its value against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
As a result, Indonesia has been faced with spiralling
inflation, growing unemployment and other serious economic and
social problems.
</P>
<P>
Tang, who arrived here Saturday for a three-day working visit,
said China believed that Indonesia will overcome its current
difficulties under the leadership of President Soeharto and with
help from the international community.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also exchanged views on bilateral, regional
and international issues of common concern, and reached consensus
on many important issues.
</P>
<P>
Tang said he will meet with Soeharto on Monday and pass an
important letter from Chinese President Jiang Zemin on to the
Indonesian president.
</P>
<P>
Tang and his party are scheduled to leave here Monday
afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
