<HEADLINE> Bishop Urge Tanzanian Christians to Maintain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Christians in Tanzania
have been urged to maintain the existing harmony and peace, and
avoid unnecessary religious confrontations.
</P>
<P>
Speaking during Easter celebrations, Bishop Basil Sambano of
Anglican church, said Christians should stick to their faiths and
ignore provocative preachings by extremists of other religions.
</P>
<P>
Bishop Sambano, who was speaking Sunday in a Easter mass at
Saint Alban Anglican Church in Dar es Salaam, said the negative
preachings against Christianity were being made by a few
individuals who seemed to have got fed with the existing peace
tranquility in the country.
</P>
<P>
The bishop's remarks came at a time when the government has
urged Moslem extremists to give up blasphemous preachings against
other religions and stop causing new. The police have arrested
hundreds of people in three riots since Mid-February.
</P>
<P>
Christians and other peace-loving people in the community
should strive to protect and maintain the harmonious environment
for the betterment of the mankind and the socio-economic
development of the nation, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Maintenance of peace is an easy job which everyone in the
country has a role to play, but restoration of a disrupted peace
is a very difficult task, he added.
</P>
<P>
He further cautioned the Tanzania community to follow
religious preachings and do away with vices such as banditry,
violence of any kind, rape, sodomy and others which are opposed
by all religions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, thousands of city residents thronged into various
churches Sunday, participating in a wide range of activities,
such as choir festivals, baptism ceremonies, holy communion, and
marriage blessings.
</P>
<P>
Despite heavy rains, prayers which ended at dawn hours, were
conducted in peace and calm.  
</P>
