<HEADLINE> Iran Urges Muslim Solidarity to Contain Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Sunday called on Islamic
countries to denounce, in one voice, any military cooperation with
Israel in order to contain the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
According to the official news agency IRNA, Foreign Ministry
spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi made the call on the second
anniversary of Israeli air raid on a south Lebanon refugee camp in
which many civilians were killed or wounded.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi said the "terrible" crime committed by Israel against
the defenseless civilians under the protection of the United
Nations indicated that Israel does not have the slightest regards
for humanitarian and international norms.
</P>
<P>
In retaliation for bomb attacks by Islamic resistance forces,
Israeli warplanes and helicopters bombed a U.N. refugee camp in
south Lebanon on April 18, 1996, killing 106 people and wounding
over 120 others.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi said that the Islamic states should try to contain
the Israeli regime through denouncing any military cooperation
with Israel.
</P>
<P>
Iran regards Israel as the major threat in the Middle East,
particularly to the Islamic countries, and frequently calls for
joint efforts against the Jewish state and urges the international
community to check Israel's nuclear facilities.
</P>
<P>
Israel, on the other hand, accuses Iran of seeking weapons of
mass destruction and sponsoring terrorism. Recent Israeli reports
claimed that Iran has acquired four nuclear warheads. 
</P>
