Northern Ireland by altering constitutional arrangements for the
province.
</P>
<P>
George Mitchell, the U.S. mediator for the Northern Ireland
talks, said he hoped the president would visit, but he added that
Clinton was waiting to see what British Prime Minister Tony Blair
and Irish Prime Minister Bertie Ahern thought best.
</P>
<P>
On May 15, Clinton is visiting Britain to attend the three-day
Birmingham meeting of the Group of Eight, namely the world's seven
major industrialized countries and Russia.
</P>
<P>
British media reports said that Clinton might offer millions of
dollars investment in Northern Ireland and provide an economic
incentive for voters to endorse the deal. 
