<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined in thin
trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index (STII) fell by 7.14 points to close at 1,586.91
points on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the stocks gave up their early gains as buying
fizzled out in directionless trading.
</P>
<P>
There is little impetus to do anything. The only supportive
factor is that interest rates may come down, one dealer with a
foreign brokerage firm said.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 143.65 million units, valued
at 230.81 million Singapore dollars (144.26 million U.S. dollars).
Declines overwhelmed advances by 223 to 98, while 271 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Malaya Resources was the most actively traded counter as it
registered a turnover of 8.83 million units. It was followed by
UniCorp which had 7.03 million shares traded. Renong was next with
6.16 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led the gainers of the day as it rose by 40 cents
to finish at 37 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sembawang and OCBC
(Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation) Foreign increased by 30
cents each to end at 13 and 9.1 Singapore dollars respectively.
DBS (Development Bank of Singapore) FR100 was up by 19 cents to
close at 3.1 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, NBT was the biggest loser as it declined by 34
cents to end at 3.04 Singapore dollars. HongFok fell by 21 cents
to close at 1.11 Singapore dollars, while Star Cruise was 19 cents
lower to finish at 1.99 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
