<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan Meets Sri Lankan Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee, met here today with a Sri
Lankan United National Party delegation headed by party leader
Ranil Wickremesinghe.
</P>
<P>
Li, also Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), noted that
China and Sri Lanka have a long history of friendly relations and
have supported, sympathized with and helped each other since the
founding of diplomatic relations 40 years ago. He added that the
two countries have also witnessed the comprehensive development of
friendly and cooperative ties in the fields of politics, the
economy and culture.
</P>
<P>
Li voiced appreciation of Sri Lanka's just stance and support
for China on the issues related to human rights, Taiwan and
Tibet. He said the CPC values its ties with Sri Lankan United
National Party
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the CPC is willing to join efforts with the
United National Party to further develop and enhance friendship
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li said that after the birth of new China, two particular
periods of 20 years are particularly worthy of
summarization. China witnessed a road of many twists and turns
during the first period lasting from 1957 to 1976, with the nation
passing through the disastrous "Cultural Revolution" which brought
the national economy to the verge of collapse, he said, adding
that the second period, from 1978 to the present, has been
characterized by a great improvement of China's comprehensive
national strength, accompanied by significant improvements in
living standards of the Chinese people and profound changes
throughout the nation.
</P>
<P>
Li explained that serious mistakes in the CPC's guiding
principles during the first twenty years accounted for disasters
during the period, while success during the second period has
resulted from the Party's adherence to and implementation of a set
of realistic lines, principles and policies suited to national
conditions.
</P>
<P>
Wickremesinghe noted that Sri Lanka and China are friendly
countries which have enjoyed friendly exchanges for centuries. He
said Sri Lanka will never forget the aid and support China has
provided.
</P>
<P>
China is a vast country with enormous potential for development
and plays an important role in ensuring peace and stability in
Asia and the world at large, said Wickremesinghe.
</P>
<P>
To develop friendly and cooperative ties with China is the
common principle pursued by all Sri Lankan political parties,
Wickremesinghe said, adding that the United National Party
attaches great importance to exchanges with the CPC and it is
willing to promote the constant development of the relations
between the two countries and their peoples through exchanges and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan delegation arrived in Beijing on Saturday at the
invitation of the CPC
</P>
<P>
The delegation is scheduled to visit Xi'an, Shanghai and
Shenzhen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
