<HEADLINE> Shanghai Starts to Announce China Containerized Freight Index </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai is now publishing the
China Containerized Freight Index.
</P>
<P>
According to municipal sources, the freight index will be
highly important for standardizing China's container shipping
market and building the city into an international shipping center.
</P>
<P>
The shipping freight index, widely used on the global shipping
market, reflects fluctuations, supply and demand trends in the
global shipping market and related markets.
</P>
<P>
Xu Lirong, president of the Shanghai Shipping Exchange, said
that the announcement of the China Containerized Freight Index
will provide reliable data for government departments to conduct
macro-controls and for businessmen to make correct decisions.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Port, the largest in China's interior area, has
witnessed unprecedent growth in its container shipping market, and
has maintained an annual growth rate of 25 percent for several
years running.
</P>
<P>
A municipal official noted that the formulation and
announcement of freight index will help boost China's container
shipping market which has been hampered by the lack of of
information and the nonstandard operations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
