<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Strengthens by 200 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's rupiah strengthened
by 200 points in Monday's trading in a positive response to the
just-signed Supplementary Memorandum of Economic and Financial
Policies worked out by Indonesia and the International Monetary
Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
The rupiah closed at 7,650/8,300 to the U.S. dollar in the
inter-bank market, some 200 points up from last Saturday's close
and also against the 8,300/8,700 in last Thursday's trading.
</P>
<P>
"It means that in four days the rupiah has strengthened by
about 1,000 points," a dealer here said.
</P>
<P>
However, several traders said, the rupiah exchange rate against
the dollar is still fluctuating, thus many dollar owners are
waiting for the right time to sell their U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On April 8, Indonesia and the IMF reached an agreement on
economic reforms in the country. Indonesian officials promised to
seriously implement the new accord in exchange for an IMF-led
43-billion-U.S. dollar bailout package.
</P>
<P>
In Singapore, most Asian currencies led by the Indonesian
rupiah strengthened on Monday on the back of a firm Japanese yen
and Indonesia's new deal with the IMF, dealers and analysts said.
</P>
</TEXT>
