<HEADLINE> China To Build National Theater in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China plans to build the Grand
National Theater, the nation's largest cross-century cultural
project, in downtown Beijing, the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The state-level theater, covering 120,000 sq.m., will be
constructed at an estimated cost of 3.54 billion yuan (420 million
US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The theater, located on the west side of the Great Hall of the
People, will include four major buildings -- the opera theater,
concert hall, drama theater and a performance center. The theater
will have a capacity of 6,000 seats.
</P>
<P>
The opera theater, with 2,500 seats, will host major
performances by world-famous opera, theater and ballet troupes.
</P>
<P>
The theater complex will also include a number of cultural and
service facilities, including an art gallery, performance research
institute, art shops, and a fast-food restaurant and cafeteria, as
well as underground parking lots.
</P>
<P>
China formulated the plan to build the national Grand Theater
some 39 years ago, with the project tabled for many years due to a
shortage of funds.
</P>
<P>
Construction will begin soon after bids for architectural and
design work are approved. Over 40 companies from China's inland
areas, the United States, Canada, Japan, France, Germany, Britain,
Italy, Hong Kong and Taiwan will submit their bids within three
months.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the theater will be completed in four years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
