<HEADLINE> College Graduates Work in Grass Roots Police Units </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Three groups of some 3,000 model
college graduates have been assigned to work in grassroots police
units across China since 1995, according to a senior official with
the Ministry of Public Security.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Chunlin, director of the ministry's Political Department,
said to participants in today's related forum that the college
graduates have injected vigor into their respective units.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that many of the graduates have not only brought
their strong points to the forefront, but have also emerged as
major assets to their units.
</P>
<P>
"The selection of model college graduates to work in grass
roots police units fully accords with the ministry's long-term
goal of strengthening the building of the national police force and
fostering grass roots police officers," said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
"It is also beneficial to improving the overall effectiveness of
grass roots police units."
</P>
<P>
The 3,000 graduates work in some 1,700 counties. or close to 83
percent of the nation's total number of counties.
</P>
<P>
Most of the graduates attended professional training at
provincial police colleges and now work in posts directly related
to criminal investigations, social order and household
registrations.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to become the leaders of China's grass roots
police units in the 21th century, said Zhu.  
