<HEADLINE> Lao Airport Opens to International Flights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- An historic Laotian city is
expecting a boost in tourist numbers with the opening of its
airport to international flights.
</P>
<P>
The airport of Luang Prabang province, which was upgraded to
international status, was opened at a ceremony by Lao Transport
Minister Phao Bounnaphone last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He said the event was historically significant to this northern
province and the whole region.
</P>
<P>
The upgrade of the airport to international flights will
facilitate the visits and co-operation between countries in the
region and the world, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Luang Prabang, where residents still adhere to traditional
practices and customs and its natural beauty is untouched, was
declared by the United Nations as a city of cultural and natural
heritage in late 1995.
</P>
<P>
It is one of the most important tourist attractions in Laos.
</P>
