<HEADLINE> Turkey to Strengthen Defense Cooperation With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Turkey will continue its efforts
to develop defense cooperation with the United States, the most
important ally of Turkey, a Turkish Foreign Ministry deputy
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a weekly press conference here, Sermet Atacanli
said that it is Ankara's hope that the upcoming visit of
U.S. Secretary of Defense William Cohen to Turkey could push
forward the friendly ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"As every body knows, there has been a close relationship
between Turkey and the U.S., especially in the area of defense
cooperation," Atacanli said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Turkey is ready to take more positive steps to
consolidate such a relationship, which is in the interests of
Turkey and the region as well.
</P>
<P>
According to the schedule, Cohen will arrive in Turkey on
Friday and is expected to meet leading Turkish government and
military officials.
</P>
<P>
Media reports here said earlier that U.S. delivery of three
frigates to Turkey and the joint production of 145 attack
helicopters might be taken up during the talks.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, the U.S. secretary of defense will also head
for the Incirlik air base near the southern Turkish city of Adana
to inspect U.S. troops stationed there.
</P>
<P>
The Incirlik air base had been used for military strikes
against Iraq during the Gulf War in 1991. Warplanes of the U.S.,
Britain and Turkey deployed there are now carrying out the
mission of monitoring northern Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
