<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Large Whale Found Dead on Somalia's Merca Beach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 13 (Xinhua)- - A very large whale has come
ashore Saturday night on the beach of southern Somali coastal
town of Merca, according to information received here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses in Merca, 100 kilometers south of Mogadishu,
said that the dead whale was longer than 19 meters and weighed
more than 10 tons.
</P>
<P>
It was said that hundreds of people from the town had rushed
to the beach to see the largest sea mammal creature that had ever
come ashore at their seashore.
</P>
<P>
Security militiamen in the town had fired several shots to
keep people away from the whale which they first thought alive.
</P>
<P>
A few seamen and experienced fishermen were allowed to get
close to the animal, which they announced was already dead.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of people then started to butcher the animal for fats
and other parts inside the animal, which they believe are
valuable.
</P>
<P>
The reason why the whale had moored is not known yet.
</P>
<P>
However, an experienced fisherman said that it was probably
injured or got sick seriously and it had come to the seashore to
evade sharks or other attacking fish.
</P>
<P>
Other sources suspected that foreign vessels had buried toxic
nuclear wastes in the sea which is killing sea creatures
steadily.
</P>
<P>
Last year, another large whale died similarly at the seashore
of Merca town. But it was not as large as this one.
</P>
<P>
The whales are not fished in Somalia. Unlike sharks, the
whale appearances are not common in the country which has the
largest seashore in Africa.
</P>
<P>
With the slaughtering of the whale still going on in Merca
Monday morning, so far, more than 10 barrels of fats have been
extracted for the use on the wooden fishing boats.
</P>
<P>
The whale fats are helpful for fishermen to stop the leaks on
their boats while fishing. But the whale meat is being distributed
to those who want to eat. Many of the ordinary Somali families do
not appreciate sea foods.
</P>
<P>
One of the eyewitnesses said that the slaughtering may take
one or two days to complete, just for its magnitude.
</P>
<P>
Many of the men butchering the whale believe that amber will
also be found in the animal's stomach.
</P>
<P>
According to the seamen, amber is something black, brown or
white in color which smells even better than the most expensive
perfumes.
</P>
<P>
"Only the lucky ones get amber once in their life time, " they
said. Amber is exported in kilograms to the Gulf countries with
very high prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
