<HEADLINE> China Offers Grain, Fertilizer Aid to DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has
decided to provide free gratis aid of 100,000 tons of grain and
20,000 tons of chemical fertilizer to the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK).
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo notified DPRK ambassador to
China Chu Chang Jun of the decision while attending afternoon
ceremonies he hosted to mark the 86 birth anniversary of late DPRK
President Kim Il Sung.
</P>
<P>
Chinese ambassador to DPRK Wan Yongxiang also notified
Pyongyang of the decision of the Chinese government today.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK side said Chinese assistance will serve as a great
encouragement to the Korean people who are struggling to overcome
temporary difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The aid also symbolizes the will of the Communist Party of
China and Chinese government to enhance and develop the
traditional Sino-DPRK friendship, it added.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK side emphasized that its party and government have
consistently advanced the Sino-DPRK friendship and will continue
to do so in the future.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK has suffered from severe natural disasters in recent
years which has resulted in poor harvests and shortages of food.
</P>
<P>
China has provided various levels of economic aid over the past
several years, including grain aid.
</P>
<P>
Observers here hold that the current move of the Chinese
government fully demonstrates its consistent stand to value,
consolidate and develop the traditional Sino-DPRK friendship.
</P>
</TEXT>
