<HEADLINE> ICBC to Loan 40 Billion to Infrastructure, Technical Innovation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC) will grant loans totalling 40 billion yuan
during 1998 to support infrastructure construction and help
upgrade the technology of state-owned enterprises, according to
today's announcement by a senior bank official.
</P>
<P>
Twenty billion yuan will go for road and railway construction,
telecommunications, power transmission networks and urban
utilitie. Selected profitable state-owned enterprises will use the
remaining 20 billion to develop high technology and improve
efficiency, according to the loan plan.
</P>
<P>
The bank will streamline its appraisal procedures for loan
applications, especially for key infrastructure projects and
technical innovation projects. The ICBC headquarters, rather than
local branches, will directly grant at least 80 percent of the
special credits for infrastructure construction, according to the
official. 
</P>
