<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Start Flight to Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing, China's fourth and
newest municipality, will open a flight to Taipei and Kaohsiung in
Taiwan in May to mark its first anniversary of establishment and
the forthcoming return of Macao to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Yunda, deputy general manager of Air Macao, told Xinhua
today that flight, which will be routed via Macao, will serve as a
bridge to further promote cross-Straits tourism, trade and
economic cooperation, as well as cultural exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The three and a half hour 2,800 -km flight between Chongqing
and Taipei will be offered on Wednesday, Friday and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Xu Zhongmin, vice-mayor of Chongqing, said the new flight is of
special significance to Chongqing, a city which served as a
temporary capital during the War Against Japanese Aggression
(1937-1945).
</P>
<P>
Some 80,000 Chongqing citizens journeyed to Taiwan in
1949. Today, however, the city is home to some 250,000 former
Taiwan residents, and more than 100,000 people from the island
province visit inland city annually, according to Xu.
</P>
<P>
Xu added that Chongqing's annual trade volume with Taiwan has
surpassed 20 million US dollars, and noted that the city is home
to some 540 Taiwan-funded businesses involving total investments
of some 700 million US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
