<HEADLINE> International Kindergarten Children Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Around 250 scientists and
specialists in childhood from different countries started a
three-day conference here Monday aimed at discovering the modern
trends of social education for kindergarten children.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the conference, the first of its kind in Kuwait,
is the Psychological and Educational Care and Needs of Current
Age. It is aimed at finding the modern trends of the social
education for kindergarten children and shedding light on the most
important problems hindering kid education, said officials who are
in charge of the organizational work.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening session, Kuwaiti Minister of Health,
Minister of Education and Minister of Higher Education Adel
Al-Sebeih stressed the importance of the international
cooperation on education for kindergarten children.
</P>
<P>
He said that surveys and statistics showed that the percentage
of children exceeded 25 percent of the total number of the
population in any society.
</P>
<P>
Children in Kuwait and Arab countries constitute a third of
the total number of the population, he added.
</P>
<P>
He noted that psychological and educational studies revealed
that children are facing some negative phenomena such as work,
homelessness, abandonment and addiction, which he said should
be carefully studied and solved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
