<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Claim 232,300 Lives in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Road accidents have claimed 232,300
lives and injured 730,260 persons in Nigeria since 1955, according to
official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Figures provided by the Federal Road Safety Commission show that
the west African country recorded no less than 964,390 road accidents
from 1955 to 1997.
</P>
<P>
The high frequency of road accidents is despite the fact that
Nigeria has one of the best highway networks in Africa, most of which
were built by the Germans during the oil boom years in the 1970s.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian sources attributed to the situation to poor traffic
management and the lack of proper enlightenment of the public.
</P>
</TEXT>
