<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Monday in the absence of fresh
leads.
</P>
<P>
The 100-quality stocks Composite Index fell 6.21 points to
666.93, the all-share Emas Index eased 1.66 points to 169.13 and
the Industrial Index shed 2.84 points to 1,211.33 and the second
board index was also down by 2.43 points to 161.63.
</P>
<P>
Losers outpaced gainers by 469 to 128 while 143 were unchanged
and 174 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover rose to 80.152 million shares valued at
152.475 million ringgit (41.831 million U.S. dollars) from last
Friday's 72.502 million shares worth 130.479 million ringgit
(35.796 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The mainboard turnover increased to 72.531 million shares
valued at 138.544 million ringgit(38.061million U.S. dollars) from
62.185 million shares worth 111.114 million ringgit (30.528
million U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The second board transactions shrank to 7.621 million shares
valued at 13.931 million ringgit (3.827 million U.S. dollars) from
10.317 million shares worth 19.364 million ringgit (5.319 million
U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market business rose to 6.796 million shares valued at
18.948 million ringgit (5.205 million U.S. dollars) from Friday's
1.012 million shares worth 5.470 million ringgit (1.502 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The market opened higher this morning but fell after an hour of
trading as investors were sidelined following poor leads to boost
market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the lower local currency ringgit Monday, which
closed at 3.6450/550 to the U.S dollar from last Friday's close of
3.600/400, further dampened sentiment.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 4.588
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products 5.899
million shares, construction 9.787 million shares, trading/service
12.818 million shares, infrastructure 230,000 shares, finance
15.013 million shares, hotels 178,000 shares, properties 13.400
million shares, plantations 1.599 million shares, mining 483,000
shares, trusts 18,000 shares, closed/fund 35,000 shares, loans
8.681 million shares. 
</P>
