<HEADLINE> Eritrea's Assab Port Increases Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Services in Eritrea's Assab
Port over the past three months have showed a 39 percent growth, the
English weekly Eritrea Profile available here reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The latest issue of the government newspaper quoted
Manager of Assab Port, Mohammed Seid Jassir, as saying that the
port handled the unloading of cargos to the tune of 288,444 tons
from 140 ships during last three months.
</P>
<P>
The manager said that at present, the amount of goods that
need to be cleared stands at 150 tons as compared to 50 tons
previously.
</P>
<P>
The manager attributed the increase of services in the last
three months to the 20 percent cut of port tariffs by the
government of Eritrea at the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The port of Assab is currently handling the needs of six ships
at a time. 
</P>
