<HEADLINE> Samsung Develops Multimedia Digital TV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 13 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's Samsung Electronic
Co., Ltd. on Monday announced it has become the world's first
electronics maker to develop a multimedia digital TV which can be
connected with numerous household multimedia products.
</P>
<P>
Samsung has made it possible to exchange sound and picture data
on a real-time basis among various audio-visual products.
</P>
<P>
The digital TV, with the same regular functions of television,
can be connected with up to 63 different audio-visual products,
such as computers, digital VCRs, through a special cable.
</P>
<P>
The new development also allows various multimedia products to
be linked together through the digital TV while a web browser is
fixed into the TV, making it easy to record and play back digital
TV broadcasts.
</P>
<P>
The specific functions of each connected product is recognized
by the digital TV, which can display those functions through its
on-screen menu.
</P>
<P>
When a PC or modem is hooked to the digital TV, it can be used
to enter the Internet.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, the digital TV is more than a "home theater
system," said Samsung. 
