<HEADLINE> U.S. President to Visit Bangladesh: Diplomat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton will
visit Bangladesh during his South Asian tour later this year,
visiting U.S. Permanent Representative to the United Nations Bill
Richardson said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Richardson, who arrived here Monday morning on a two-day visit,
made the announcement while making a speech on "Making Democracy
Work in the 21st Century" at the Bangladesh Institute of
International and Strategic Studies.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after an hour-long meeting with
Bangladeshi Foreign Minister Abdus Samad Azad, Richardson said he
discussed about 20 topics with the Bangladeshi side, such as
American investment in the south Asian nation, and the Chittagong
Hill Tracts peace accord Dhaka signed with the tribal rebels in
the region last year.
</P>
<P>
Richardson will also visit India and Pakistan during his South
Asian tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
