European single currency euro, the leftwing majority and rightwing
opposition of France have seen their division lines over euro
reappear within their own camps. The draft law on the reform of the
statute of the Bank of France marked the resurgence of the
divisions, as the deputies of the centrist Union for French
Democracy and Socialist Party voted for the law, while the
Communists and one fourth of the deputies of the Rally for the
Republic voted against. 
