<HEADLINE> Indonesia Pledges to Push Forward its Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
expressed the hope that his country will always push forward its
friendly cooperation relations with China.
</P>
<P>
The expression was made by the president when meeting with
visiting Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan at the Bina Graha
presidential office here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The President reiterated that Indonesia's "one China" policy
will not change.
</P>
<P>
Tang, who arrived here last Saturday for a three-day working
visit at the invitation of his Indonesian counterpart Ali Alatas,
appreciated Indonesia's policy, saying the new Chinese government
will continue its good-neighboring policy with Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, both sides exchanged views on strengthening
economic and trade cooperation between the two countries in
current situation.
</P>
<P>
Tang had a three-hour meeting with Alatas on Sunday, during
which he pledged that China would provide assistance it can to
Indonesia to help overcome monetary crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
China offered to give medicine and food worth 3 million U.S.
dollars as well as provide a 200 million dollars export credit
facility to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto thanked China's valuable aid, holding that it will
benefit Indonesia's efforts in overcoming current difficulties and
backing to its healthy track of development.
</P>
<P>
The president also appreciated China's decision on no
devaluation for its currency, RMB, noting that it will help
Southeast Asian countries to stabilize their economies and
monetary sectors.
</P>
<P>
Tang said the Chinese government and people concerned about and
sympathize for Indonesia which is suffering from severe monetary
crisis. He believed that the Indonesian government will certainly
overcome its difficulties under the leadership of President
Soeharto and through its efforts and the help from the
international community.
</P>
<P>
Tang and his party will leave here for home Monday afternoon.
</P>
</TEXT>
