First Section issues, dropped 8.44 points, or 0.67 percent to
1,242.91.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was Monday's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Transactions were dull since European markets remain closed Monday
for Easter holidays and ahead of Wednesday's meeting in Washington of
finance ministers and central bankers from the Group of Seven (G-7)
industrialized nations, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,328 issues listed on the First Section, losers outpaced
gainers 691 to 363, with 172 remaining unchanged. 
