relations, he said, because it is hard to maintain long-term
political stability without economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki told Zhu that South Africa is willing to continue
consulting with China on bilateral economic and trade
collaboration and that the further development of economic and
trade ties will benefit the two countries and economic recovery in
Africa as a whole. 
