<HEADLINE> Swede Wins Third Women's World Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Elisabet Gustafson won her
record-tying third women's world curling championship for Sweden
on Sunday with a 7-3 victory over Denmark's Helena Blach Lavrsen.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish rink, including third Katarina Nyberg, second
Louise Marmont and lead sweeper Elisabeth Persson, avenged an
upset semifinal loss to Denmark at the Olympics in Nagano.
</P>
<P>
Gustafson had to settle for bronze in curling's official
Olympic debut this year, while Blach Lavrsen took silver.
</P>
<P>
Canada, gold medalists in Nagano and winners of 10 of the
previous 19 women's world championship, finished third by beating
Norway 10-2.
</P>
<P>
In Saturday's men's final, Canada won world gold with a 7-4
victory over 1997 champions Sweden. 
