<HEADLINE> France Benefits from Investment in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- French businessmen have built 80
joint ventures with a total investment of 200 million US dollars
in Tianjin, the largest port city in north China.
</P>
<P>
The total import and export volume between Tianjin and France
has surpassed 100 million US dollars, said a municipal government
official in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Carrefour, a leading chain store dealer in France, opened two
supermarkets in Tianjin at the end of last year. The daily
transaction volume of the two stores exceeded 2 million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
The two bank branches opened respectively by the Banqoue
National De Paris and Credit Lyonnais in the city reported good
returns last year.
</P>
<P>
French investment covers a wide range of subjects including
manufacturing, finance, commerce and public utilities.
</P>
<P>
The Remi Martin Co. set up the first joint venture in Tianjin
as early as in 1980. Now the winery turns out 20 million bottles
of wine annually, netting a profit of 100 million yuan. The French
side offered to prolong the term of contract from 11 years to 100
years. 
