<HEADLINE> East China Province to Build More Roads </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province
plans to spend 72 billion yuan on building new roads in the next
five years.
</P>
<P>
The investment will be mainly used in building 36 trunk lines
and expressways, said vice provincial governor Han Yuqun.
</P>
<P>
When these projects are completed, the total mileage of roads
in Shandong will be extended from the existing 800 km to 2,642
km. by the year 2010, ranking first in China, he added.
</P>
<P>
This year, 19 new projects with a total length of 1,261 km will
start construction with an estimated investment of 9.6 billion
yuan. Work on seven expressways will also start within the year.
</P>
<P>
As a leading economic powerhouse, Shandong ranks third in China
in terms of gross domestic product. The province set its economic
growth rate at nine percent this year.
</P>
<P>
Shandong plans to invest 14 billion yuan a year in 1998 and
1999 in a bid to make infrastructure construction suit economic
growth.  
</P>
