<HEADLINE> Third Round of Inter-Korean Talks to Start in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The North and South Korean
representatives rescheduled their morning talks to afternoon in
Beijing, with the hope to improve bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
According to the schedule, the third round of the
vice-ministerial level talks, which opened here Saturday
afternoon, should have started in a local five-star hotel at 10:00
am. But it was postponed to 15:00 pm, sources say.
</P>
<P>
This is the first inter-Korean government level contact in
nearly four years between the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK) and the Republic of Korea (ROK).
</P>
<P>
Both sides have agreed to discuss all the issues proposed,
including supplies of food and fertilizer from ROK to DPRK,
reunion of separated families, exchange of special envoys and
implementation of the North-South Basic Agreement.
</P>
<P>
Chun Kum Chul, counsellor of the DPRK Administration Council,
heads a five-member delegation, while Jeong Se Hyun, vice-minister
of the ROK National Unification, also leads a five-member
delegation.
</P>
<P>
China is the only country which maintains formal diplomatic
ties with all three political powers involved on the Korean
Peninsula -- the DPRK, the ROK and the U.S.  
</P>
</TEXT>
