<HEADLINE> China Eastern Air Group to Start New Routes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China Eastern Air Group will
start two new international routes in addition to improving
domestic routes this year.
</P>
<P>
The airlines, headquartered in Shanghai, will start
Shanghai-Okayama air route beginning June 30, and
Beijing-Shanghai-Paris air route beginning July 7.
</P>
<P>
Regular flights will be available Tuesday and Friday on the
Shanghai-Okayama route, but with the Beijing-Shanghai-Paris route,
regular flights will be arranged Tuesday and Saturday, according
to an executive of the air group.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai-Okayama air route will be the air group's sixth to
Japan. Currently, the group is operating air routes to Tokyo,
Osaka, Fukuoka, Nagasaki and Nagoya. Paris will be the fourth
European city after Munich, Brussels and Madrid on the air group's
regular service from Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the air group will also increase existing weekly
flights on the Shanghai-Beijing-San Francisco line and on the
Beijing-Shanghai-Sydney line by adding one more plane to each of
them. It will also increase flights on the Shanghai-Fukuoka air
route from five to seven a week.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern, which has taken over the China General Air
Company, will start 20 new air routes to cities where its
subsidiaries are based, while increasing flights on existing air
routes connecting provincial capitals in east, south, northeast
and southwest China and operating three air routes of the China
General Air Company.
</P>
<P>
The air group is also operating four international cargo air
routes which include Shanghai-Tokyo, Shanghai-Osaka and
Shanghai-Beijing-Brussels. 
</P>
