<HEADLINE> S.Korea to Import Iraqi Oil in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 13 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's LG-Caltex Oil
Corp. will import 500,000 barrels of crude oil from Iraq in May,
the company said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The crude oil, which is due to reach South Korea on May 15,
will be at a price of 10.50 U.S. dollars per barrel, some 0.3
dollars cheaper than those in other Gulf countries.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first time for South Korea to import crude oil
from Iraq since the Gulf War in 1990, when the United Nations
imposed an economic sanction on the Arab country. Since then,
South Korea has banned imports of Iraqi oil.
</P>
<P>
South Korea's forthcoming import of Iraqi oil follows a United
Nations' resolution last December to ease restrictions on Iraq's
oil export. 
