<HEADLINE> Electronic Publications Thriving in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to the development of
CD-ROM technology, electronic publications have been thriving in
China.
</P>
<P>
Before 1994 only 12 kinds of CD-ROMs were produced, but 7.53
million pieces in 1,025 kinds were turned out last year, according
to Yu Yongzhan, deputy director of the Press and Publication
Administration of China.
</P>
<P>
So far supervisory bodies have been set up in 29 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions of the country to oversee
the electronic publications, Yu said, adding that in December
1997, the administration issued a regulation on the management of
electronic publications and some big cities including Beijing and
Shanghai have formulated local rules.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the considerable increase in quantity, the
quality of electronic publications has been greatly improved, Yu
said.
</P>
<P>
The CD-ROMs cover documentaries, educational materials,
entertainment, and the collection of back issues of newspapers and
periodicals.  
</P>
