<HEADLINE> More Saw Mills to Be Privatized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Three more state-owned saw mills
will be added to the privatization scheme in Myanmar, The New
Light of Myanmar newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The saw mills of the Forestry Ministry are in the country's
Sagaing division where more than two dozen similar saw mills have
been handed over to private entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
In early January, some 42 state-run factories under the
Ministries of Industry, Livestock Breeding and Fishery, and
Commerce, and other two livestock breeding farms as well as 76
cinemas of the Information Ministry were also designated to be
privatized, according to an earlier official report.
</P>
<P>
Since Myanmar announced privatization of 51 state-owned
economic enterprises (SEEs) in the first phase in January 1995,
the privatization process has been underway in various forms
including auctioning and leasing out the SEEs or establishing
joint ventures with local and foreign entrepreneurs or operating
either under buy-back or counter-trade system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
