<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SW China Province to Cut Number of Spindles in Textile Factories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Province plans to cut the
number of spindles by 120,000 and lay off 14,000 workers in the
textile sector this year to reduce losses.
</P>
<P>
The first 20,000 spindles were destroyed recently in Chengdu, the
provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the effort is to avoid 60 million yuan in losses
this year, according to a provincial textile official.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan has long been a textile center in southwest
China. It will focus its reduction efforts mainly on Chengdu,
Mianyang, Neijiang, Leshan and Zigong, its five most important
textile producers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the campaign to avoid overproduction will have to
give equal attention to finding employment for the laidoff workers,
the official said.
</P>
<P>
The textile sector has been one of China's biggest money
losers. In recent months, spindle-reduction has become a
nationwide campaign.  
</P>
</TEXT>
