<HEADLINE> Ballerini Wins Paris-Roubaix for Second Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Italian Franco Ballerini surged 45
kilometers from the finish to win the Paris-Roubaix classic for
the second time on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Mapei rider broke away from the pack and remained on his
own for an hour to become the 17th rider to complete the double.
</P>
<P>
He finished in a time of six hours 55 minutes and 16 seconds,
four minutes 20 seconds ahead of team mates Andrea Tafi and
Wilfried Peeters. Mapei also completed a sweep of podium places
here two years ago.
</P>
<P>
The event, known as the most demanding one-day race, was made
even tougher this season by heavy rain. Crashes on muddy lanes and
countless punctures reduced the field from 198 starters to fewer
than 40 finishers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
