<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Military Exercise to Enhance Army's Combat Skills in Modern War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China's armed forces has launched
a new round of military exercises to enhance its capability to
cope with high-tech modern wars.
</P>
<P>
According to sources with the People's Liberation Army (PLA),
the training intends to acquaint PLA officers and soldiers with
the means and ways to win regional wars employing high-technology.
</P>
<P>
The PLA Headquarters of the General Staff and the General
Logistics Department have held lectures and seminars on
high-technology used in military fields and logistical work in
high-tech and regional military conflicts.
</P>
<P>
PLA military commands across the country, the navy and air
force have also opened training classes for senior officers to
learn about advanced technology.
</P>
<P>
The comprehensive military drills represents another milestone
in the PLA's modernization drive, according to sources.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese army initiated the first of its comprehensive
drills in the 1950s after the PLA won the war of liberation. The
intensive training helped lift the then largely guerrilla PLA to
the standards of a modern army.
</P>
<P>
For the first time, the army received basic training in
combat using atomic and chemical weapons. However, the principles
as well as training courses followed those of the former Soviet
Union.
</P>
<P>
The second large-scale drill was conducted in the 1960s. By
then China had designed its own training programs. The drill was
culminated in a series of competition involving combat skills at
various levels which produced thousands of outstanding officers
and soldiers.
</P>
<P>
In the 1970s, the PLA exercises focused on developing skills to
fight wars involving tanks, warplanes and airborne forces, in
addition to wars using atomic, chemical and biological weapons.
</P>
<P>
The last massive military exercises which were carried out in
the 1980s stressed PLA services and the ability to coordinate
efforts as well as the command skills of PLA officers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980413.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
