<HEADLINE> Pierce Wins Amelia Island Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Fourth-seeded Mary Pierce of
France beat sixth-seeded Conchita Martinez of Spain to win the
Bausch &AMP; Lomb Championships held at Amelia Island, Florida, on
Sunday
</P>
<P>
Pierce dominated the final two sets to claim the title with a
6-7 (8-10), 6-0, 6-2 victory.
</P>
<P>
The two-time runner-up in the last two years said, "it feels
good to win it after three times in the final."
</P>
<P>
Pierce, who beat top seed Lindsay Davenport in the semi-finals,
rebounded from the first set loss when she abandoned trying to
trade groundstrokes with Martinez from the baseline and began to
vigorously attack net.
</P>
<P>
The French player, who is 13-2 for the year and won the Paris
Indoors title in February, earned 79,000 U.S. dollars for the
victory that will move her world ranking to the fifth on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The ninth-ranked Martinez, who reached the Australian Open
final in January, has 28 career titles, including Wimbledon in
1994, but she hasn't won a tournament since Moscow in November of
1996.
</P>
<P>
Martinez, the 1995 champion, won 31,500 dollars as runner-up in
the the two hour, one minute match.
</P>
<P>
Pierce had 44 winners to just 11 for Martinez, but she gave
away her big advantage with a whopping 51 unforced errors compared
to 25 by the Spaniard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
